inn1.comm: back of a length on leg stump, Gilchrist tries to tickle it fine but mistimes it to short fine leg for a leg-bye
good length outside off stump, he gets half forward and drives and gets an inside-edge to square leg
good length outside off stump, defended towards point
good stuff, short of a length with some good purchase off  the deck, Hayden stands rooted and decides to leave it on length, and it deviates over the top of middle stump
overpitched outside off stump, he leans into his drive but cant  beat Samuels at cover
good length outside off stump, he gets forward and drives back down the track, mid-off moves quickly and gets to it
back of a length delivery goes down leg stump for a wide
good length moving in from middle stump, Gilchrist doesnt move his feet much but squeezes it out to cover with a firm 'NO' back to Hayden
short of a length on the stumps, he moves around and works it straight to midwicket
back of a length on off stump, Gilchrist stands and works it to midwicket again, Taylor hitting a good length already
but thats another wide well down leg stump, which Taylor doesnt approve of, visibly
back of a length on leg stump, Gilchrist works that away behind square for a couple
beaten by one that lands on a sweet length just outside off stump, the ball does enough off the pitch and Gilchrist is suckered into a tame drive away from the body

more width offered this time and he goes through with a square-drive, not timed to perfection, but its in the gap between cover and point and they steal runs as Sarwan gives chase and hauls it in comfortably
good length delivery quite outside off stump and Hayden just shoulders arms to it
bends his back into this one, a back of a length, quicker delivery outside off to stump to which Hayden again shoulders arms
similar length and carry but much closer to off stump, a confident Hayden shoulders arms once more
back of a length on off stump, Hayden gets up and defends it back to Powell, who's bowling well here
back of a length on middle and leg this time, Hayden has no option but to defend it back to the bowler
back of a length outside off stump, left alone
back of a length on leg stump, poor line, Gilchrist shuffles and works it in the gap on the leg side and Collymore gives chase, an easy three to the batsmen
good length well outside off stump, Hayden thinks about driving it and ends up loosely chasing it to get beaten
beaten by a slower one that swings away from off stump, Hayden stands rooted and just wafts at it, very close to getting an edge
tighter line this time, good length on the stumps, Hayden jams bat and pad together and defends back to Taylor
good length just outside off stump, Hayden stands and defends to the offside
back of a length outside off stump, now he squeezes it to the off side and Bravo moves quickly from short extra cover to field it, and Hayden still remains on 0

edged and gone! Powell bangs in a shorter one at a good pace, lands on about middle and leg and moves in a tad, Gilchrist hops up and defends, maybe he was trying to get bat out of the way, but there's the thinnest of edges through and Ramdin moves to his right and holds a good catch low down! Gilchrist starts to walk before Asad Rauf raises the finger and West Indies have drawn first blood
another shortish one down leg side, Ponting looks to put it away but the ball clips the pads and he has to settle for leg-byes
good length outside off stump, Ponting walks into a confident-looking defensive shot to cover
back of a length on about off stump, Ponting gets up and defends it back to Powell
good length on off stump, there's the trademark lunge forward and whip through midwicket for Ponting to open his account
good ball, full in the blockhole and Ponting has to react quickly to dig it out back to Powell's left
good length outside off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives nicely down the ground to mid-off
another bad ball down leg stump, just drifting too far and thats called wide
short of a length outside off stump, just tapped wide of point and Hayden gets off a duck
good length just outside off stump, Ponting gets over it and defends it to point

too full and straying down the pads, Ponting shuffles and clips it well past short fine leg, ball looks certain to be a four, but Chanderpaul dives superbly and saves two on the ropes, good to see that kind of effort
fractionally overpitched outside off stump and Ponting lunges forward to drive down the ground, mid-off dives over it and has to scramble to haul it in and thats an easy three
slower delivery angled across off stump, stays low too as Hayden flashes at it and misses
short of a length outside off stump, he gets behind it and defends to the off side
good length on off stump and he drives superbly back down the ground, too well timed and the ball ricochets onto the nonstrikers stumps
back of a length on middle and off, he shuffles and works it to the on side
back of a length, moves in from outside off stump and Ponting has to hurry to work it off the hips in front of square for runs
good length on middle and off, thats a confident on drive but straight to mid-on
bang, thats six! Powell decides to bounce him but the lack of carry does him in, Ponting just swivels on one foot and hooks it over deep backward square leg for half a dozen! Shot!
overpitched outside off stump, the slower ball, Hayden drives to cover
more width on offer and Hayden gets onto one knee and flashes a firm drive in the gap between cover and mid-off, albeit in the air for a seconds, and picks up his first four
and again! Hayden receives a slower ball, too full outside off stump, and drives it smack in that same gap for another boundary
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden waits for it and plays with soft hands, tapping it in front of point for a quick single
slower one, striving for the yorker outside off stump, well done and Ponting defends it back to the bowler
good length outside off stump, he gets forward but mistimes the attempted cover drive, chopping into the ground in front of point
good length outside off stump, Hayden leans into his drive but cant beat Samuels in the covers
short of a length outside off stump, he mistimes his cut to point
too full outside off stump and Hayden square-drives that past point for a couple
good length outside off stump, driven to cover
short of a length and coming in from outside off stump, Ponting uses soft hands to drop it in front of the off side fielders and steals a single
oh ho! Now Hayden, already standing outside his crease, walks down the track and hammers a good length delivery back over Powell's head for four! Thats arrogance!
slower one smack on the money just outside off stump, a hint of movement away from Ponting, who covers his stumps and holds back the bat

madness! Good length on the stumps, Ponting gets over it and drives in front of mid-on and sets off, Hayden stands unmoved and sends him back, Pontings halfway down the track, turns and sprints back to his end and manages to beat the throw
full and wide, he gets down on bended knee and crunches a powerful square drive but a superb effort at point saves four runs, great stuff from Bravo
good length on off stump, defended back
good length outside off stump, Ponting plants the front leg down the track and short-arm punches that in the over just wide of mid-off for four
sublime! Too full on off stump, Ponting gets well over it and just effortlessly flicks it over square leg for four
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden stands and chops it to point
good length outside off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives to cover, cant beat the man there though
again he has a walk down the track, whipping a good length delivery from outside off stump towards square leg
back of a length outside off stump, Ponting gets bat and pad together as he rocks forward to defend to cover
good length ball on off stump, Ponting gets forward and presents a textbook defense back to Powell
a low full toss outside off stump and Ponting doesnt let it go, just leans forward and drives it between cover and point and the ball speeds across what is a sluggish outfield for four
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden stands up and defends to backward point
back of a length on middle and leg, Hayden places it wide of Lara at midwicket and steals a single
overpitched on middle and leg and Ponting flicks through midwicket, theres a man back on the ropes so now chance of a four
good length on middle and leg, Hayden gets forward and flicks it right to the squaer leg fielder
back of a length on off stump, he stands up and defends back down the ground, 'NO MATE' is the call back to his partner
short of a length on left stump, Hayden gets up and works it off the hips just wide of square eg and calls for an easy run
fraction width offered and Hayden cuts it wide of gulley down to third man
good length outside off stump, no movement whatsoever, Ponting walks into his defense to cover
good length outside off stump, and what does he do? He stands there and whips it from outside off through midwicket and mid-on and the ball runs away for four! Hah!
now a tad fuller outside off stump, this time Ponting comes forward and defends stoically
back of a length on off stump, Ponting gets behind the line and defends back to Taylor
good length outside off stump and Ponting drives, ending up with an inside-edge back past leg stump that trickles down to fine leg
back of a length on the stumps, Ponting shuffles across to off, exposing leg, and taps it wide of square leg for one
back of a length on leg stump, clipped past short fine leg for a brace
back of a length on middle and off, driven back towards Collymore's left
a tad fuller on off stump, he gets his head down and defends back to the bowler
good length outside off stump, no room to work with and Hayden defends it back to Collymore
angled down leg stump, Hayden looks to flick but misses and the umpire signals wide
back of a length on the stumps, Hayden goes back and across and drives wide of Lara at mid-on for a single to keep strike
good length moving in from about off stump and Hayden gets back and turns it straight to midwicket
good length on off stump, Hayden has a step across and tickles it around the corner to Collymore at short fine leg for one
short of a length outside off stump, Ponting goes back on the toes and punches, away from his body, to cover

and a piece of brilliance gets rid of a brillant batsman! A good length delivery outside off stump, Ponting lunges forward and drives into the covers and sets off, Sarwan collects the ball and has one stump to aim at, and doesnt miss! A superb throw that catches Ponting just short of his crease, even though he was going full stretch! Great work!
almost! Back of a length outside off stump, Hayden gets back and drops it in front of point and set off, Clarke is really struggling but a wayward throw misses and he's home!
back of a length delivery moves in a wee bit from outside off stump, Clarke stands and works it to mid-on and doesnt want the run..wise move from the youngster
good length outside off stump, defended to Sarwan at cover
Hayden walks down the crease and Collymore digs it in short, Hayden pulls over midwicket out to the man on the ropes
fuller length outside off stump, Clarke drops the angled bat down on it and squeezes it to backward point
good length on off stump, he plants the front leg forward and flicks across the line to midwicket
good length outside off stump, Clarke gets forward and runs it down to third man for two, wants the third but decides against it, wisely
drifts to leg and Clarke flicks it around the corner down to Chanderpaul at fine leg
back of a length outside off stump, up on the toes goes Clarke, punching to cover and telling Hayden to stay where he is as cover swoops in
good length outside off stump, he gets forward and pushes right to Chanderpaul at mid-off and calls for the run, and luckily for him a poor throw lets him off, had it hit he was a goner
short of a length outside off stump, Hayden opens the face and places it to the right of Smith at point, but he dives and saves runs
back of a length on off stump, Clarke stands up and drives back to Taylor
good length on off stump, Clarke shuffles and drives to Lara at mid-on, calls for another mad single, then sends Hayden back, and Lara's throw just misses! Hayden wouldve been out by a meter!
good length on the stumps, worked to the man at midwicket
good length on leg stump, worked back towards Collymore
good length on middle and leg, he's cramped for room and taps it back to Collymore's left
back of a length on the stumps, played back to the bowler again
short of a length on off stump, he waits for it and then rolls the wrists over it, placing it in the gap at midwicket for a well-run two
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden looks to come onto the front foot but has to adjust, playing it off the backfoot to point
back of a length on the stumps, Hayden is again cramped for room and has to defend back to Collymore, who's bowled a very tidy over
fuller one on off stump, Clarke gets over it and flicks straight to Samuels at midwicket, who fields well
back of a length outside off stump, this time he gets well forward and drives to cover, though not with any perfect timing
good length on off stump, comes in, Clarke rolls the wrists well and works it past Lara, who misfields, and the ball trickles over the ropes past mid-on
back of a length on the stumps, again worked to the man on the leg side
good length outside off stump, Clarke gets a good stride forward and places it into the cover, waits to see if Gayle can get to it, and when he doesnt Clarke calls for the run
from around the wicket, bangs in a shorter delivery which Hayden works to mid-on for another riskly single...these Australians are sure trying to get themselves run out today
back of a length outside off stump, he stands up and drives to cover
now he has a walk down the track, the ball is shorter than anticipated and he has to try and adjust, ends up flicking awkwardly to short fine leg
good length outside off stump, Clarke drops the hands on it and runs it to backward point and sends Hayden back
back of a length on off stump, Clarke comes forward and drives back to Collymore
good length outside off stump, he gets to the pitch and drives well to mid-off
hello! Clarke shimmies down the track and collects a good length delivery on the full, helping himself to a lofted four down to the long-on ropes
good length outside off stump, Hayden gets forward and drives in the off side gap and collects and easy couple as the sweeper collects it
good length on off stump, Hayden shuffles to off and looks to flick through midwicket but doesnt time it well enough, ends up placing it to mid-on
now he steps down the track, Powell drops short, but Hayden has too much power on it, placing the jabbed pull over in the air between mid-on and midwicket for four
good length on the stumps, he defends back to Powell
back of a length angled across him, he gets half forward and defends to cover
once more, he steps out of his crease, again Powell sees him and tries to drop short, but Hayden's all over it, pulling through midwicket and mid-on for another authoritative boundary
tossed up on off stump, Clarke shuffles and flicks across the line for one to midwicket
tossed up outside off stump, Hayden gets a leg well across and then shoulders arms as the ball spins in
flatter and fuller, Hayden defends it
tossed up outside off stump, Hayden comes forward and defends
quicker one now, Hayden shuffles and looks to flick it away but gets beaten by the pace
he oversteps, the ball is full and Hayden defends back to Gayle
shorter, flatter trajectory, Hayden has to adjust to drive towards mid-on
dragged in short down leg stump, as if in anticipation that Hayden will dance down the track, and he pulls it down to fine leg for one
good length just outside off stump, Clarke lunges forward and with soft hands just drops it in front of the off side fielders and calls for the run
full ball down the stumps, Hayden looks to clip it, theres a noise and Ramdin takes it , then they all go up in appeal, umpire Rauf stands unmoved and then after a few seconds signals wide
back of a length outside off stump, pushed off the back foot into the covers for one
good length outside off stump, Clarke comes forward and drives to cover
back of a length outside off stump, Clarke gets across and drives straight to mid-on
fuller one now outside off stump, Clarke gets across and flicks superbly in the gap at mid-on to pick up four, really intelligently done
flatter one, Hayden dances down and flicks through midwicket for two
tossed up, he shimmies down and collects it one the full, driving smack straight down the ground between Gayle and the stumps for four and thats his fifty, well played, sir!
short and wide, he rocks over it and cuts hard past backward point
flatter one outside off stump, Clarke waits for it and plays late towards gully
shorter and flatter outside off stump, Hayden gets behind it and defends back to Gayle

fired in quicker on a length outside off stump, Hayden hops up and gets rapped on the pads outside the line, they appeal but thats not out due to the inside-edge and a run to boot as the ball trickles to point
back of a length outside leg stump, Hayden tickles it past short fine leg for an easy brace
back of a length on the stumps, this time he walks to off stump and taps it to the leg side but Collymore's quick to get to it
he steps to leg, exposing the stumps, Collymore fires it in short on leg stump, Hayden has to adjust to dabble it off the pads for one to short fine leg
short and wide, Clarke crunches hard but an acrobatic Smith at backward point collects it
good length outside off stump, Clarke gets to the pitch and drives right to Gayle in the covers
overpitched outside off stump, he uses the feet and comes out to square-drive wide of point out to third man
short and flat on off stump, he goes back and punches to midwicket
good length on off stump, driven back to Gayle
shorter one spins in, Clarke plays it late off the face of the bat to gully
flatter one, Hayden dances down to free the arms, drives out towards mid-off for one
flatter one, Clarke waits for it and drives to mid-on for one
spins into him from a length, he waits for it to come into him and opens the face to run it wide of Bravo at backward point, cheeky
back of a length outside off stump, Clarke drives past point out to the man on the ropes
on leg stump, Hayden tickles it to short fine leg for one
short of a length on middle and leg, Clarke adjusts and semi-pulls through backward square for a well-judged two, helped by the fumble at fine leg
gives himself room to smack this one in the gap between cover and mid-off for a thumping four!
good length on the stumps, he whips it through midwicket out in the wide open spaces, easy as they come
slower one, full on off stump, worked right to midwicket
hah! Hayden dances down the track and hammers this through midwicket for four!
he oversteps, firing it down leg stump and Hayden helps it on its way
fired in flat, Hayden uses the feet and flicks into midwicket for easy runs again
tossed up outside off stump, Hayden comes forward and defends to the covers
a mis-hit as Hayden charges and has to adjust to the length and flicking with the inside-edge to short fine leg
short and flat, Clarke makes room and slams it down to long-off for one
quick, flat and spinning into leg stump, Hayden waits for it and tucks it off the pads for one wide of square leg
back of a length on leg stump, Hayden's already backed away and so he has to drive down the ground for one
well bowled, the slower one almost in the blockhole, Clarke too backs away to leg and has to adjust to keep it out
good length on middle and off, Clarke shuffles across and flicks it around the corner for one
back of a length on leg stump again, worked fine for one
back of a length on leg stump again, easy pickings for Hayden, who works it to square leg for one
slower ball on off stump, Clarke gets over it and flicks it to square leg for two
flat outside off stump, Hayden shuffles across and gets one to square leg easily
tossed up on off stump, flicked but right to midwicket
short, flat and Clarke makes room to cut past point for one
short and wide, he chops into the covers for one
tossed up, Clarke gets forward and whips it to Lara at mid-on
short and flat outside off stump, Hayden works it through midwicket for a very well-run two
drifts to leg and Clarke puts him away for one out to backward square leg
good length on leg stump, Hayden waits for it and taps it into midwicket for another milked single
too full on leg stump and Clarke flicks past square leg for one, Hayden says no the second as the fielder moves well
back of a length on leg stump once again, and Hayden coolly works it to square leg for one more

and Bravo gets his man! Clarke plays half-cock forward to one that moves in appreciably from outside off stump, gets rapped on the leg, everyone appeals and after a good thought umpire Rauf raises the dreaded finger
good shout! Symonds stands rooted, and plays all over one that swings in from middle and off, clearly did too much to take leg stump, and Rauf shakes his head.
looped up outside off stump, Hayden reaches for it and drives it between extra cover and long-off to collect a single
tossed up on off stump, Symonds defends back to Samuels
flat on leg stump, worked to square leg
again full down leg stump, Symonds gets off the mark with a nudge to short fine leg
flat outside off stump, Hayden comes out and drives to cover

he comes out, dancing down the track, Samuels drops it wide and short, Hayden goes through with his shot, one-handed, and somehow manages to get enough bat on it to send it high in the air between long-on and long-off!
full on the pads, Symonds flicks but straight to square leg
back of a length outside off stump, he stands up and defends with an inside-edge to square leg
angled down the leg side off a length and its called wide, duly
a tad fuller on middle and leg, Symonds on-drives to Lara at mid-on
back of a length outside off stump, Symonds gets onto one knee, ducks somewhat, and swats it through square leg for one...odd but effective
slower one comes out a full toss on leg stump, surprising Hayden, who hops up and keeps it down to midwicket, Symonds is well down the track and has to scamper back
on the pads once again, and Hayden works it past square leg for a couple as Powell gives chase
tossed up, driven to Lara at mid-on
slower one outside off stump, Symonds waits for it and then dabs it to backward point for one
flat outside off stump, Hayden gets to the pitch and drives into the covers for one
flat down leg stump, picked off the pads into midwicket for an easy single
biff! Short, flat outside off stump and Hayden rocks back to flat-bat that powerfull down the ground for four and he moves into the nineties
tossed up, he gets to the pitch and drives into the covers with soft hands to retain strike
good length on leg stump, Hayden drives to mid-on and calls for one immediately
back of a length on off stump, Symonds stands deep in his crease and pushes it back to Bravo
slower one goes all wrong, short outside off stump and Symonds picks it up early, swatting it over the infield for four past mid-on
back of a length and moving in from outside off stump, he plays it late and runs it down to third man to raise the 200
good length on middle and leg, Hayden gets well over it and flicks into midwicket for one
good length outside off stump, again Symonds runs it off the face of the angled bat and gets one to third man
tossed up outside off, driven to long-off and they get two
flatter on off stump, flicked out to long-on for one
flatter outside off stump, Hayden gets to it and drives straight to point
full on leg stump, clipped well through midwicket to calls of "HUSTLE, HUSTLE" and thats a well-run two
tossed up outside off stump, driven down to long-off for one
edged and gone! Samuels fires one wide of off stump, Symonds stands there and looks to bring the bat down late to cheekily run it fine, but ends up with a thin edge that Ramdin neatly snaps up!
back of a length outside off stump, Hayden waits for it and dabs between cover and point for one to get to 99
overpitched outside off stump, Hussey drives straight to Sarwan in the covers
overpitched again and this time he drives straight to mid-off
back of a length, moves in from leg to off and Hussey gets behind the line and defends to point
driveable length on the stumps, Hussey does so but hits the nonstriker's stumps, had Powell gotten a finger to it Hayden was a goner
back of a good length outside off stump, Hussey reaches for it and drives into the covers

there it is! Second hundred of the tournament for Hayden! Stands in his crease and drives one to mid-off, waits to see if the fielder can get to it, and then calls for the run. Superb effort, remember he took some 19 deliveries to get off the mark, and he's gotten here with a strikerate in the 90s. Great knock from Haydos.
tossed up, Hussey has to reach for it and drives back to Samuels
flatter one, now he reaches and drives to Lara at mid-off
again he's struggling, driving to point
fired in full and flat, Hussey digs it back out to Samuels
tossed up, he comes out and drives to long-off to get off the mark
shot! Short outside off stump and Hussey pulls off the front foot, slamming it over midwicket for four!
fuller on off stump, taken on the full and driven down to long-off
fuller one angled across off stump, Hayden stands rooted and squeezes two out past backward point
well bowled, in the blockhole, Hayden rolls the wrists over it to jam it out
fuller one outside off stump, Hayden frees the arms and drives into the covers where Lara drives to his left and saves three runs
beaten by the slower one, angled across off stump, as he stands and dabs the bat at it
width offered, he cuts but ends up chopping into the ground before point
tossed up, he gets to the length and punches down to long-off
he tries too much and ends up firing one well wide of off stump for a wide
flat in the blockhole, Hussey manages to chip it into midwicket for one
slower one, tossed up, Hayden waits for it and then opens the face to place it in front of backward point for a single
quicker one outside off stump, checked drive into the covers
quicker one again, Hussey tries to dab it and gets beaten
he makes room and lifts a fuller one just over mid-off for four, shot!
close! Hayden steps out and lofts one down to long-on, where Sarwan misjudges it as he comes in from the ropes, and the ball just evades his outstretched arms for four!
fuller one in the blockhole, Hayden flicks across the stumps for one to square leg
good length outside off stump, Hussey square-drives wide of square and knows theres two for the taking from the word go
bowled 'em! Hussey reaches out to drive a very full delivery and ends up dragging it back onto off stump! A tame dismissal and Powell's gotten a second in his final over!
back of a length on off stump, Watson gets his head down and defends back to Powell, who finishes a pretty decent spell given the occasion and situation
tossed up, Hayden gets to the pitch and drives into the covers, where Lara fields
flat on middle and leg, driven to mid-on for one
tossed up on off stump, Watson gets forward and plays across the line to pick up one into midwicket
flat, yorker-length ball outside off stump, Hayden jams the bat down and steers it to backward point
tossed up, Watson comes and takes it on the full and flicks across the line but right to Sarwan at square leg
another yorker outside off stump, Hayden drives back to Samuels
full on leg stump, clipped out to fine leg
yorker outside off stump, Hayden opens the face and runs it down to third man
low full toss on off stump, driven into the covers and he sprints down the track for one
back of a length outside off stump, Watson stands there and opens the face to manufacture runs fine, but mistimes it
drifts across to leg stump and Watson flicks past square leg, Smith moves quickly on the ropes and saves two
good length on off stump, Watson gets across and rolls the wrists over it to pick up one to midwicket
flat outside off stump, worked into the square leg region for one
full and flat outside off stump, driven to Lara at mid-off
change of pace, fuller and quicker, Hayden swings across the line and misses
flat again outside off stump, Hayden drives into the covers
tossed up on off stump, Watson drives down to long-on for one
low full toss outside off stump, Hayden drives but finds Lara at cover this time, just three overs from the over
short of a length outside off stump, Watson cuts hard into the point region and the batsmen scamper a single
super shot! Hayden clears the front leg, gives himself room and slams one from outside off stump just over Chanderpaul at long-on for maximum
now he goes off side, making room again to free the arms, and even though he loses control of one hand, he gets enough on it to hit it over extra cover for four
big, better, blasted! Wasnt full at all, Hayden makes room, backs himself and sends this sailing some 15 rows back behind the sight screen! Massive!
slower one, back of a length outside off stump, he opens the face and places it wide of backward point for one
full in the blockhole, Watson's given himself room to hit and ends up driving down to long-on for a single
full on middle and off, clipped past mid-on for one
low full toss on off stump, Hayden swings across the line and places it wide of mid-off for four more
fuller and wider, Hayden now has a swing at it and gets beaten
shot! Uses the pace, jamming the bat down, with an open face, and runs it down to third man for four

Hayden you beauty! 150 is up for the big man! Tossed up outside off stump, real slow, Hayden isnt to the pitch but backs himself to clear the ropes, and he does so with ease, swatting this high over cow corner for another dinger!
he oversteps and thats a freebie
he opts for a real short one, which Hayden helps along its way past short fine leg
overpitched outside off stump, driven to Lara at cover and sets off immediately for the run
drifting down leg, Watson stands and eyes the deep midwicket ropes, swings at it but ends up with a leg-bye to the off side
aha! Hayden! Gives himself room outside leg stump and smashes this through the covers for four
full on middle and leg, he drives via an inside-edge to square leg
great improvisation from Watson! Ambles across to off, goes down on one knee, and scoops this high around the corner for six! Top shot!
slower ball, on a yorker length just outside off stump and Watson is beaten on the drive
full in the zone, no room to work with, and Hayden scoops this in the air straight down the throat of Samuels at long-off, and an excellent innings comes to an end
slower ball again, outside off stump, Watson looks for that cheeky paddle around the corner as he moves across to off, but cant pull it off
well bowled! Slower one just outside off stump deceives Watson, that was so close to off stump
overpitched outside off stump, Watson drives along the ground of mid-off
full down leg, Hoggs already taken guard well outside leg stump and cant work it away, ends up with a leg-bye to square leg
full in the zone, well bowled, Watson can only dig it out to mid-on for the single
low full toss outside off stump, Watson flashes and gets a thick edge down to third man for one
back of a length outside off stump, Hogg backs away and looks to flay it through the off side but connects with air
dropped in short, Hogg chops that past backward point out to Bravo in the deep for a couple
yorker ends up a low full toss on the stumps, Hogg drives through cover out to the sweeper and picks up two more
well bowled, yorker in the zone, Hogg gets bat on it and squeezes one into the covers
full outside off stump, Watson comes well outside the line in an attempt to paddle it fine, the ball hits him on the full and he steals a leg-bye in front of point
lovely one, really slow on a length outside off stump, Watson has to wait ages for it and then slashes at it, the ball takes the edge and drops before Ramdin
full down leg side, wide called
another attempted yorker turns out a slow full toss on off stump, Watson waits for it and slams it over midwicket for four
shot! Overpitched outside off stump, Watson gets down on bended knee and drives in the off side gap for four
low full toss on the stumps, swatted out to wide long-on for just the single
slower one again, just outside off stump, Hogg goes down as he heaves across the line, misses and Watson calls for the run, a direct hit comes in but he's safely home
and he ends off in style! Bravo goes wide with the slower ball, Watson hangs on it and drives on the up between cover and point, and thats four to take Australia to 322 for six!

inn2.comm: better, but too wide of the off stump to trouble the left hander who watches it swing past him
and a poor start from Bracken, firing this down the leg side. West Indies are off the mark
ooh, there we go, angling into Gayle before it swings away from him. Gayle came forward, quite tentatively, but his firm forward defence was soundly beaten
oh well bowled, that's a boomeranging outswinger from Bracken. Immense lift, off a good length, too
tighter line, but again there is prodigious outswing for Bracken. Gayle is wise to it now, and shoulders arms
left alone outside off - a little too wide of the off stump to trouble Gayle
well, I think Bracken can count himself lucky that wasn't called a wide. Left alone outside off
and, as with Bracken, Tait's first ball is flung down the leg side
clipped off his legs but Hussey fields at midwicket like a Jack Russell, scampering to his left
good line this from Tait, rising up on Chanderpaul's off stump and he goes back and across to defend off the back foot
a full-bunger down the leg side rightly called a wide
on off stump, left alone
oh dear. This is even wider of the leg stump. A comprehensive wide, if there is such a thing, swinging wider still
a touch straighter - full, fast on leg stump - and Chanderpaul clips it off his toes down to fine leg
very well bowled this time, on middle-and-off and Gayle has to jab down on it quickly - his crab-like stance rather suggesting the ball kept a little low
clipped off his toes straight to midwicket
very wide of the off stump - I'd have called it. But then that's why I'm typing about the cricket and not officiating. Left alone by the batsman
lovely drive, waiting on the back foot before driving it calmly through cover
that's close, coming back into Chanderpaul who is rapped on the pads. Replays suggest I'm completely wrong, it wasn't that close, and was rising over his stumps. In fact, it pitched outside off too
squidged out into the covers off the back foot
driven with more of a flourish and an extended follow-through, but it clunks off the bat without timing to mid-off
swinging into Chanderpaul who is again rapped on the pads, beaten by the swing, but no cause for an appeal there
that's zipped past Gayle's throat, albeit wide of his off stump...but an encouraging sign from Tait, getting good bounce off a length
there's the line, on middle-and-off and swinging into Gayle who is really hurried into a defensive poke
full, swinging into him and Gayle is finally off the mark with a squirted drive past the bowler
oh and Chanderpaul goes on the pull here - too full to be pulling, perhaps? - gets it off the toe of the bat and it spoons in the air over the bowler. Very fortunate not to find mid-on
quick. Quick ball, 91mph (146ish kph) outside off. Chanderpaul goes for a Caribbean slash, but misses it by miles
gone! Full, straight, swinging into Chanderpaul's pads who plays all around it
the wrong line, drifting down leg and Sarwan nudges it to leg to steal the strike
pushed out into the off side off the back foot
ah, fine bowling from Bracken, pitching this up just a touch. It swings into Sarwan who, to his credit, plays it late off the back foot, angling it past gully
the day's first solid forward defence from Gayle. Nicely behind it, head right over the ball
a good length this - really nagging length: nearly driveable, but not quite. Gayle is forward in defence
firmly blocked out on the front foot once more
check-driven to mid-off. No chance of a run there. Australia's fielders are positively buzzing at the moment.
on leg stump and, with strong wrist action, he whips it through midwicket
a nasty riser from Tait. That was a heavy, fast ball really spitting up on Sarwan who fends it off his chest
crunched to Ponting's right at mid-off but he dives, and saves
clever, intelligent bowling, sending this wider of Sarwan to tempt him - and he is tempted, going for a huge flay outside off. And misses.
quicker still (92mph. 148kph) but Sarwan is up on his toes, cutting to point. But straight to point
neatly clipped off his toes, if not as well timed as he'd like, straight to midwicket
left alone outside off. Bracken continues with this annoyingly wide line of the off stump
better. Cutting back into Gayle who is solidly behind it
pushed out with a greater flourish into the covers, but still no run
check-driven on the front foot to mid-off
good line, and full too, Gayle defends it off the back foot
too straight, Gayle works it off his legs to fine leg
inevitably it's pitches on a length, cutting back into Gayle
and a wicket with his second ball for McGrath. Short of a length, but Gayle premeditated it, getting a top-edge off a pull and it's skied to Watson at mid-on
back and across, defending this solidly
what a ball from McGrath. That spat up at Samuels viciously who took his eye off the ball which struck him just below the grill
ah, lovely flourishing drive but straight to cover
classic McGrath line-and-length; frustratingly accurate, on off stump, and it keeps a little low on Samuels
on leg stump - again it keeps low - and it's prodded off the back foot
ooh, cuts this into Sarwan who is late on it, defending it off the back foot
straighter this time, of driveable length, and Sarwan cracks it to mid-off on the up
excellent line, on off stump - the early boomerang swing has been reduced to just a "rang" - and it's firmly blocked out by Sarwan
prodded off the back foot to cover
cracked to cover. But straight cover
shot. Cover driven with elegance, authority, through cover
cuts back into him and he jabs down on it late
driven on the up, but straight to cover

oh dear. That is a truly dreadful shot, skipping down the pitch, he was nowhere near to the pitch of the ball. Trying to hit McGrath back over his head, a one-handed, unbalanced top edge handed a simple skier to Symonds at cover
left alone outside off
and it's firmly defended on the back foot
that one's darted down the off side, on a good length, and the batsman takes his arms and shoulders them
jabs quickly down on to this one, straighter, in line with off, and rising, so he plays off the back foot
even straighter, bang on middle, and Lara shapes to work that one into the midwicket, quick hands as ever, but stops on the shot
great channeling from Bracken, on off this time, right up there and again Lara is made to defend
outside off and Lara can leave that one easily enough. So he does
off the mark at last with a tickle to midwicket
stays over the wicket to the lefthander, by the way, and Lara jabs that one down off the back foot
even a mere push of a drive to mid-off, as with this one here, is sumptuous to watch. McGrath bends his back, gets a fingertip to it, and does enough to take the pace off the ball
oozes that one into the short midwicket this time
short and that's played down and round behind square
defended down off the back foot
driven slowly to mid off
short, on off, and that's jabbed down off the back foot into the covers
short and that's tickled into midwicket off the back foot, the batsman leaving his crease, but getting back quickly as he realises there's no run on

they look for a quick single off an inside edge and there's a direct hit but Umpire Rauf's into his position quickly and saw that the batsman was well in. The Aussies half-heartedly appealed, there, but Lara was so safely home he was up the stairs tucked up in his pyjamas
jabbed down off the back foot
played out to point
worked out to a very wide fine leg
dances down, stops, and stuns the ball on the front foot, playing defensively down into the track
pushes that one across the lefthanded Lara, a touch of room and it rises; the batsman defends it down, this time off the back foot
across him again, a little bit straighter, and Lara is forced to defend yet again
very straight, and that's defended right down
...until now, dragging that a touch short and that's wristed from outside off stump in front of midwicket, Watson gives chase and hunts it down inside the boundary
way too much width, trying to adjust to the righthander, but there's a good double act from Watson and Symonds on the cover boundary and that's relayed back

short, and Sarwan latches on to it, sending it only as far as point. I can't relay what Sarwan said, this being before the watershed, but let's just say his language was a touch industrial, frustrated at missing out
pushed in front of midwicket
on off, up there, and Sarwan does well to even manoeuvre that into the leg-side, wristy wrists agogo, but yet again he can't pick the gap. I think the stump mic was turned off that time, just in case
on a good length, driven into the covers
strays on leg and that's driven in front of midwicket
strayed down off and that's played out to the man on the fine-leg boundary
too much width - don't bowl there to him! - and that's cracked through cover on the up, top shot
much better, straight and fuller, Lara squeezing that into the on side
again, up there, even fuller, and Lara can only defend, in an orthodox manner
Lara makes obvious his intent to leave that one, whirling his bat round his head as he does so
another leave, slightly less theatrical, but he decided early again - the ball once more pinging outside off and floating a touch away from him
down that off channel again, the batsman completing a third leave in a row
crashed away behind point for two easy runs
a fumble at midwicket - will they? Won't they? They will, and it's easy in the end
stays over the wicket and that's just full enough to prevent Lara swinging out at that one
driven out to the covers this time where it's picked up easily enough
quicker one, outside off, an attempted yorker but he got his line wrong, too wide and Lara's not interested
carved into the covers, but straight to the man. There's a menacing inner ring of fielders waiting to snap something up and the pressure's still building
flings that one in at a good length, and straight, and that's defended down
a touch of width, and Sarwan cuts that down on the rise, straight to point
short and Sarwan fails to get it away, jabbing it into the covers. He's giving himself a strict talking to, as the frustration grows
pushed right up there and defended on the front foot
short, attempted bouncer and that's well ducked under
on leg and swished to square where Mr Cricket pretends to throw it back into the keeper. He loves his cricket
dropped. Now that would have been a really good take - still, it was a definite chance from a short ball taken by Sarwan from off to just in front of mid-on and Hussey dives, but shells
tries to work it to mid-on again
tucked into the midwicket region
slower legcutter and Lara leans into that, strong and with consummate timing, and he smashes it through cover
hammered straight to Symonds at cover, there was a misfield as it bobbled just in front of him, and that allows the single
straight, with a touch of room, and Sarwan stands tall to ease that one in front of midwicket, but doesn't get much power on it
grunts with the effort - "Ehh" - but still bangs that dully down leg, the batsman gamely swivelling round to have a go, yet is too late on the shot
more grunting, but it's straighter and that's defended down this time
more grunting, like being at Wimbledon on a bad day, and that's pushed right up there, the ball driven back to mid-on

short and pulled strong, and brilliantly, in front of midwicket. Not much wrong with that delivery from Tait, just short of a length, but Lara helps himself, and dismissively - disdainfully, even - swats that one away
clever thinking from Tait, Lara dancing down and Tait answering his charge by cramping him up
defended into the covers this time
just outside off and that's check-drived straight to the man at cover
whipped off his legs and, oh that's a marvellous piece of fielding from possibly Ponting at short midwicket, throwing down the stumps - and Bracken does well to save an overthrown four
cracked into the covers, but straight to the man
full and straight, worked to mid-on for a single
mighty, mighty close there. On a length, too full to be pulling - but Lara is desperate now, and goes for an almighty heave-ho over midwicket, missing it completely
banged into the pitch and it's left alone this time
what a remarkable shot that is from Lara. Slayed through cover - almost falling backwards as he does so, the bat swirling with an extravagant follow-through and it scudded across the turf for four
in the air, but it flies over point and lands short of deep extra cover
that'll be a wide, no worries there. Flung down the leg side with an audible grunt by Tait
on leg stump, and worked calmly to mid-on
really crisply hit off the back foot. Sarwan plays that stroke very competently, just punching it really, never trying to hit it too hard
miles wide of the off stump, although not quite a Harmiwide. Tait looks as confused as anyone
short, very short, on leg stump. Lara pulls, gets a thin edge around the corner and it races down for four. Fine batting
bosh! Lara at his best there, flaying this on the up behind square for another four

oooh, the tide is turning here. Lara's flicked the switch. A fine ball on off stump, Lara tries to work it to leg - gets a thick outside edge which first slip would've poached with ease...but Australia are slipless
just short of a length, and an excellent line here which he works greyly to midwicket
Sarwan takes a step down the pitch here; Watson sends down a bouncer in repost which Sarwan evades
pushed into the covers
on off stump, Lara just pushes it to mid-off and grabs a single
elegant, flourishing drive. For nothing.
chipped down the ground for the most facile of singles
full - and wide - allowing Sarwan to go down on one knee, propose to the ball, before smashing it wide of cover
clunkily driven straight into the ground. Symonds dives, quite brilliantly, to save a run
cracked to point off the back foot
again wider, but greater spin here, turning back into the right hander who punches it back to him
Lara charges him, smashing it on the full to Hogg who actually does really well, diving - tongue still hanging out of his mouth - and getting a hand to it
defended on the front foot
defended off the back foot
good length; wrong line, too straight, whipped off his hip
short, rising onto Lara's cranium who keeps his eye on the ball - almost lining up his head with it, in fact - before paddling it around the corner
Sarwan gives Watson the charge, crashing this to mid-off but he again can't find the gap there
and there we go: short, Sarwan pulls in front of square, timing it really well
Sarwan back-cuts this to Clarke at point who, brilliantly, throws down the stumps, forcing Sarwan to hurry his bat back into the crease
pushed down the ground
impatience has cost Sarwan. Charging Hogg, taking him on the full, he flat-batted him straight to midwicket. A careless, wasteful shot and the pressure has told
lovely ball - quicker, on leg stump and he's right forward to it, defending it with firmness
short, wide, cut off the back foot to point
ooh and he's done him in the length there; charging him, Bravo is forced to jab this down but he gets a thick outside edge which flies just short of gully
punched to silly point
short of a length, he rocks back and punches it into the covers. And they steal a decidedly cheeky single
remarkable shot! Punched on the front foot past the bowler for four. Beautifully timed
pushed to cover - oh dear, they're going for a single. Here comes the throw from cover, and he's just home
on off stump, neither a threatening line or length - no pace either - and Lara clubs it down the ground
too straight, whipped-creamed off his legs for a single
and he's done it, dropping this into the leg side and stealing the strike
not a bad shout indeed from Hogg. Lara gave him the charge but replays confirm not only my blindness, but my deafness too, as Lara clubbed that into his foot
another roar from Hogg as Lara is rapped on the pads, but it's down the leg side
and again Lara charges him, but Hogg fires it down quicker and straighter. Clipped for a single
bravo, Dwayne. Just short of a length and he's quick to rock back and crunch it off the back foot. Not quite as well timed as he'd like, but he's fleet of foot
short and down the leg side
again short, and slow, Lara pulls it while down on one knee
crashed off the back foot to point. Only just short of point...
too leg side from the ageing fast bowler, clipped back to him
and it's pushed out to long-off
lazy shot - another complacent, unbalanced drive, not getting on top of it and it spoons straight to Ponting at cover
defended on the front foot
pushed out to cover
beaten. Cracking ball, jagging back into a meek defensive prod
down the leg side, Lara sweeps and misses
the wrong'un, turning away from the left hander who cuts it to third man and gets a single. And his fifty
calmly, elegantly driven through cover. Full toss, four. As it should be.
better length from Hogg, rushing onto the batsman who goes back to defend
excellent feet from Ramdin, skipping back and hammering this into the covers
comes forward to meet this wider ball, clumping it without power to cover
chops down and an inside edge crashes into the ground, threatening to take the off sticke. He gets away with it this time
pushed into the covers
width from McGrath and that's hammered off the back foot with a crashing blow through cover. We like that
straight, and McGrath, like a doting father, tucks him right up. No lullaby, though
straight again, but Ramdin takes a stride to off to swish it back to leg and there's an easy run there
short and Lara connects cleanly, pulling that down to square
poked down off the back foot
puts that on the money and Gilly says that was "Nice, George".
waits on the back foot, and makes a smidge of room for one which is wide already, to work that through point
doesn't quite get hold of that one, teeing off with an off-drive

Hogg has taken a blow of another kind, that one dibbled into the gully and Clarke shies that over to the non-striker's end where it bounces up and, let's just say, awkwardly at Hogg. Hogg smiles, or was that winces?
tickled to midwicket
pushed right up there, straight, and that's dug out well
what a short, Lara just waits and, well, that was magnificent - he deftly touches that away through the vacant first slip; deliberately and sweetly as you like. And you do like
played out behind point
short and belted towards midwicket
driven to the man at long-off this time
wide outside off, Lara kneels down and late cuts that off one knee down to third man

clears the man at long-off - well clear - with, well you can probably guess but I'll tell you anyway, a really sweet straight drive... comes out of his crease and latches on quickly and sends that high and straight
a let-off - Lara going for the repeat but not quite getting the distance, but that drops short of the man at extra cover
shuffle-drives that one off his front foot to long-off
oh, Hogg nearly does him with one that's pitched up there and he nearly falls into that shot, nearly
overthrows - a desperate shy at the striker's end from Watson after Lara tried to sweep on one knee, not cleanly connecting
neat shot, walking into that and rushing it in front of midwicket for two
short, slower, and the batsman does well to give himself room, tucking back to time that well behind point off the back foot and it races away
angles across Ramdin and that's crashed in the air through gully but evades a diving Clarke
outside off and that's guided easily away to deep third man
outside off again, a touch straighter to the righthander who works that down to third man
outside off and that's cut into the ground, Lara looking hungry for more runs
wider and that's worked down to third man and the crowd love it - tooting their horns in appreciation
pushed right up there and that's poked down off the front foot
driven to mid-on

a huge appeal and that's a tame effort from Lara, a full delivery and he came down the track, yorking himself in the end, and that raps him on the knee at daisy height. The newly shorn Hogg is loving it, as are the Australia players, who swarm around him
that angles across him from leg and defended down
defended down
defended into the covers
cheeky - the batsman coming outside off, presenting the face of his bat to sweep behind square
wide and that's worked into the covers
right up there and driven out to long-on
guided down through third man
more width, Symonds struggling with his line here, and that's dinked into the off side
gives it a touch of flight and that's flatbatted up through the covers. "Ca.... aaatch," cries Gilchrist, sounding oddly like his voice is in slo-mo
worked off the back foot to point and it's zoomed back in underarm
drags that a touch short and that's a bit of a despairing - yet at the same time forceful -sweep round to square
now this is a nice shot! Down the track, left, right, left and that's struck very well over cow corner
gone! Leg break which would have gone on to clip off and middle about four-fifths of the way up the stumps. Australia continue to close in on victory now - it's just a matter of time
oh, nearly took the edge there as that one turned right back in from leg and popped up a touch too, a devil to play
another tricksy ball, but the batsman does well to stab his bat down on that one
turn and bounce outside off and that's worked behind point
outside off and that's dibbled into the covers
turned to midwicket
up there and well dug out
low, full, and spanked over long-on
thrown back in from fine leg, but they can't prevent the second

didn't pick the googly and that's a very good shout indeed from Gilchrist who whips off the bails before you can say "Third umpire". But Taylor, rightly, got the benefit of the doubt - after several replays from different angles
turns in from outside leg, the batsman has room, in turn, to turn that in front of midwicket. Lots of turning, like a driving Test or nothing (ah, test... too much cricket!)
worked out to point
defended tidily
shuffled into the covers and there's a quick single
pokes the blade towards that one, misses, but wasn't near connecting, so no drama
single to long-on
pushed to midwicket for a quick single
neat stroke, lofting it over cover for four
worked off his legs through midwicket
defended on the front foot
worked around the corner
ooh, swept aerially but it falls short of the man running round from fine-leg
off the back foot, he works it to cover for a quick single. Tait thinks about throwing down the stumps...but decides against it
big turn there, back into the right hander who chops to gully
very neatly swept around the corner
slightly wide of the off stump but a crisp drive finds point
shot. In the slot, he slog-sweeps it over midwicket. That's what we like
full and straight, punched to a wide mid-on
again pushed to mid-on but timed it too well to get a run
pushed back to the bowler
and he's gone. Big indrift for Symonds there, foxing the batsman who tried to sweep and was trapped in front
the wrong line, drifting down the leg stump and it races for four. Pretty sloppy from GIlchrist
pat-pads this to cover
a full toss which is pumped to long-on to end the over
worked off his legs for a single
crashed on the front foot, but there's no power in the stroke
close! A huge swing and a miss, the batsman appearing to glove the ball mere millimetres from his off stump
pushed out to mid-off, to Symonds, who shies and - breaking news - misses
well that's a fine stroke with which to bring up a combative fifty, uppercutting it wide of third man. Excellent cricket
turned around to fine leg and they pick up a single. No, they're going for two - and they'll get it easily
pushed out to cover
gone! A slower ball, on middle stump and just angling across the batsman who tried to smash it over the bowler's head...a thin outside edge which Gilchrist gobbles
excellent ball, squaring him up but he plays it well, angling it down
and a play-and-a-miss
gone! No, ignore me. A big swish over cover but it lands safe
neatly defended on the front foot
quick, spearing into the batsman who gives himself a touch of room, pinging it powerfully to mid-off
not quite sure what he was attempting there...he took a good step outside his leg stump, trying to uppercut it...missing it by at least a metre
gone! And it's all over. Full and straight from Tait; Powell takes another step outside leg, and is comprehensively bowled
